CQDs synthesized by calcination of ammonium citrate were obtained as a dark brown residue. Dispersion of this residue in absolute ethanol gave rise to a dark brown solution which emited green glow under UV irradiation (Fig. 1
                        ). Upon investigation of sol-gel derived ZrO2 NPs by SEM (Fig. 2
                        -A & B), mostly a spherical morphology was observed with an average particle size of 40 nm. However, upon more resolved analysis by TEM (Fig. 2-C & D), the presence of a minor fraction of rod-shaped particles were observed as well.
